{
  "texts": [
    "This largely mimics the process used in Przybyla (2020), and extends the work of Litterer, Jurgens, and Card (2023) on identifying 'news storms' in the NELA corpora to a larger time-span, and a larger set of publishers.",
    "In this section, we describe various dimensions along which we believe covariate shifts likely to occur, and which are feasible to simulate using misinfo-general.",
    "We consider a total of 6 specific generalization axes.",
    "Time based generalization measures the extent to which changes in publisher style affect a model's predictions.",
    "The publishers considered in each split should be held constant to avoid confounding with different publishers."
  ]
}